page.title: 09Ecology/Housing
page.content: {ECOLOGY }The ground under our area is mainly clay. Oak and Ash trees make up the woodland with willows on lower ground. {HOUSING}There is a predominance of brick built houses, over half being built before 1939. There are very few flats, but an equal number of detached, semi-detached and terraced houses. {LISTED BUILDINGS}A Listed Building is of special architectural or historic interest under the Town and Country Planning Act 1971. In this village there are some Grade 2 and Grade 3 buildings.
